dct_description_sm: Filing title: Henderson, Ky.-Ind. Edition of 1916. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows Henderson and Vandergurgh counties in Kentucky and Posey County, Indiana. Includes map in lower margin showing areas surveyed by Goodlove, Herrington, and Gehres. Contour interval 20 feet. Engraved 1916 by U.S.G.S. Surveyed in 1914. Reprinted 1947. R.B. Marshall, chief geographer, W.H. Herron, geographer in charge, topography by C.W. Goodlove, R.M. Herrington, and W.S. Gehres, control by Corps of Engineers, U.S. Army, U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey, E.C. Bibbee, S.R. Archer, Marvin Lee, G.T. Hawkins, and J.R. Ellis. Surveyed in cooperation with the state of Kentucky.
Imprint: [Washington, D.C.] : Department of the Interior, U.S. Geological Survey, [1947]
Dimensions: 45 x 42 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:62,500
